The paper deals with the representation and interpolation of light field videos using neural networks, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The use of neural networks also suggests a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the processing of visual data, which could also place it under multimedia (cs.MM).
